    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Shiny white crystalline compound used in photography as a toner and to remove stains from negatives. Capable of dissolving silver salts, thiourea is often an active ingredient in silver-dip tarnish removal solutions. It is also used to accelerate the vulcanization of rubber. Its composition is the same as that of urea but with a sulfur atom in place of the oxygen atom.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
